content.description:
An unrepeated line on the steep face between Pitty The Fool and Block and Tackle. Apparently the moves are quite good, according to Zach. Some of the bolts are hard to spot, but they are there.

Get on it, and help me update the description!

climbs.name: Pitty Da Fool
climbs.fa: TR Rick Shull 2007, FFA: Zach Miller '10

content.description: Begins up the steep leaning arete on the left side of the cliff. First few bolts are on the left, then the route transfers to the right on lower angle terrain. Super technical and powerful. Stick clip needed.
content.location: Left side of the main face

content.description: Climb the first few bolts of Block and Tackle, then just before the climbing gets tricky, cut right following a line of bolts spaced close enough to keep you off of the ledges. Pull the lip and climb mossy slab. Originally graded 5.10d, we think 5.11b is more accurate for that wildly incredible crux.
content.location: Farthest right route, starts on Block and Tackle

content.description: Super technical moves up a blocky dihedral. I felt there were three tricky sections of the climb, but the physical crux comes at the final dihedral. Be ready for a surprise at the "last bolt"
content.location: Right hand side of the Mr. T Wall
